,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,XAG product_f934c1fb-3d10-b9cd-14bc-486358791c9c,Product,B13960S XAG Smart Battery,

The 2021 B13960S Smart Battery is compatible with all of XAG's 2021 Agricultural System (Compatible P40, P80, P100, V40 Agricultural UAV) . With 13 high capacity Lithium polymer cells and a BMS integration module, it features real-time monitoring of status information including voltage, current and temperature, as well as charge protection. Specifically, the battery can give immediate feedback to the load side during use. In case of battery low or failure, the BMS system will send an emergency stop signal initiatively to ensure the electrical safety of the load side.

 

All prices are GST exclusive

,bb4003_1f56c74f7845428d93ac5686b0534a5a~mv2.png,Parts - Propeller;Parts - P30 Compatible;Parts - All,14-002-00171C,Non-XAG Brand,349,,TRUE,PERCENT,0,3,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Safety Instruction,"

[IMPORTANT]

For the Operators who are utilizing the customized Carbon Fibre Propeller and Spinner, it is essential for the Operator to inspect the Propeller assembly on a frequent basis (Every 10 Flights). The operator should inspect and ensure
1. There is no spacing between the Propeller and the Propeller Spinner.
2. The Screws are not loose.
Spinner
Carbon Fibre Propeller Blades MUST use the Aerospace Grade Aluminium Spinner.
Washer
Each Propeller (XAG or After-Market Propeller) Blades MUST be correctly placed and covered by 2 Washers.
Screw Padding
There are two types of pads included in the Propeller package and must be all placed on each screw when installing.
Tightness of the Blade
During the installation of the Screws on the Spinner, it shouldn’t be loose but it shouldn’t be too tightened as well.
The level of tightness should be maintained to the level where you start feeling resistance and require forces to tighten the screws + 1 Turn.
Maintenance
The washers need to be checked periodically, replace it when thickness of washers is reduced.
Perform Pre-flight checks as always

XAG® XCam® MultiSpectrum

Remote Sensing to Facilitate Precise Decision-making

With XCam MultiSpectrum camera, 4-spectrum HD crop images can be captured as well as HD RGB images. The NDVI map aligned in pixel level can facilitate on-site agriculture decision making. The farm prescription map generated by XAI can be applied directly to the XAG P series UAS for autonomous plant protection operation.

 

Equipped with an 1-inch 20-megapixel RGB camera + a four-spectral channel high-sensitivity CMOS sensor, the system can capture 4-band HD multi-spectral images of crops and HD RGB (visible light) images. The global shutter can precisely coordinate with RTK navigation to synchronise images with the high-precision position data in milliseconds. The images from five different channels are aligned automatically, and the photosensitivity sensor is calibrated automatically. Accurate remote sensing image of farmland can be processed on-site, what you get is more than what you see.

A Legend, Enhanced Capabilities

P20 Plant Protection UAS, inherited the strong capabilities from its previous generation, optimized and further enhanced based on the 1 million hectares of commercial agricultural operations over 50 types of crop. P20 is an autonomous Plant Protection UAS which provides precision spraying while being more stable, longer endurance, and better topographic adaptability.

 

RADAR TERRAIN TRACING AND OPTIC POSITIONING

Millimeter-wave radar can accurately trace terrain fluctuation up to 30 meters above the ground at all kinds of terrain. This ensures that P20 can fly stable at the set relative altitude above the perceived terrain type. 40° coning-angle terrain-tracing keeps variation≤10cm. When GNSS RTK or GPS is interfered, the optic positioning module will be activated automatically to reassure flight safety, even at nights

 

AUTONOMOUS FLYING, EAST TO LEARN

Autonomous flying, easy to learn and operate. P20 can be operated without laying hands on a manual controller; Supports swarm operation with one pilot operating multiple UASs, significantly improves operational efficiency. Infrared sensors allow night operations, making the most use of time during busy farming seasons.

 

INTELLIGENT CONTROL, PRECISE AND FLEXIBLE

XAG JETSEED Granule Spreading System

An automatic spreading machine designed for seeding, fertilisation and plant protection, JetSeed™ is engineered to set free the agriculture production world. Compatible with the latest XAG® P30 Plant Protection UAS. Featured with high-speed, focused airflow. Granules such as seeds and fertilisers, propelled by powerful, stable jets of air, are projected effectively and precisely to wherever needed. Harnessing XAG SUPERX®3 Pro autonomous flight control system and RTK high-accuracy navigation network, JetSeed™ elevates its spreading precision to an unprecedented new level.

 

Breakneck efficiency.
XAG JetSeed™, a flying spreader, can effectively dispense granular seeds, fertilisers or pesticides on up to 12 acres of land per hour, a task that would take 150 labors to complete. Simply via a smartphone, the fully autonomous flight mode enables XAG JetSeed™ to smoothly operate in many different environments that the ground-based spreading machinery is difficult to handle.

 

Every granule counts.
Through projecting streams of powerful, stable and high-speed air, XAG JetSeed™️, configured with P30’s centimeter-level flight accuracy, brings every granule to the place it is supposed to be. The embedded rolling feeder guarantees a uniform output needed. Farmers will no longer face the problems of uneven seeding or overdose.

 

XAG® P30 Plant Protection UAS, the power behinds.
XAG JetSeed™, easily mounted into the highly modularised XAG® P30 Plant Protection UAS, is ready to embark on its task within minutes. Empowered by the centimeter-level Dual-RTK technology, XAG JetSeed™ optimised the spreading accuracy to its maximum.

 

Built-in smart feeding mechanism, never gets stuck, always feeds evenly.
XAG JetSeed™ supports different sizes of granules, from 1mm ~ 10mm. The rolling feeder can utmost ensure a demanded dosage, by compensating its output volume to the flight speed. Besides, two independent powerful mixers are installed above the feeder to avoid cluster.

 

Controlled, high-velocity air brings ultimate spreading uniformity.
Harnessing the Bernoulli principle, the 8 Electronic Ducted Fans (EDF) generate high-speed, focused airflows at up to 18 m/s. This creates a pressure difference that induces granules from feeder, whilst the granules, fueled by the accelerated airflows, are rapidly and precisely dispensed to the target area without being affected by environmental winds. Also, the spread width can be easily adjusted by tuning the air velocity or changing the jet nozzles.

XCam + mobile App:
